			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	From what I have noticed in the past it works like Kwang-11.<br />
<br />
It creates a field.  Multiple fields do not add and are not treated as seperate fields (they only increase the area of coverage).<br />
<br />
So, a single battleship with Insanity Field Generator does just as much damage to an enemy fleet (800 points) as 20 fleets of 40 dooms each all equiped with insanity field generator.<br />
<br />
Also of note is that the 800 points is dealt to the enemy fleet just like regular damage, so if the first ship absorbs it (most likely), no other ships in the fleet are affected.  This is pretty lame considering that Kwang-11 affects ALL ships in the fleet.  I understand that the fields do not compound damage (it's a field), but I don't understand that the damage isn't dealt to each and every enemy ship (not fleet) in the field.<br />
<br />
My information is from a few sets ago when I actively tried the device on several different ship designs.<br />
<br />
It does stop single gunboat screening fleets(that's about it though).			   <P align=right></P>
			</TD>
